div.h1: E820 Memory Map: Physical Memory Layout

p.strong: BIOS-provided memory regions at boot time

div.p: Type Values: 1 = Usable RAM 2 = Reserved 3 = ACPI Reclaimable 4 = ACPI NVS (preserve) 5 = Unusable (defective)

CRITICAL: Kernel MUST parse this map before allocating frames! Allocating from reserved regions corrupts: BIOS data structures unpredictable boot failures ACPI tables power management breaks MMIO regions hardware malfunction
Low Memory Detail: 0x0000 - 0x03FF: IVT (1KB) 0x0400 - 0x04FF: BDA (256B) 0x0500 - 0x7BFF: Free (~30KB) 0x7C00 - 0x7DFF: Bootloader (512B) 0x7E00 - 0x9FFF: Free (~8KB)
BIOS Data + Video RAM 0x000A0000 - 0x000FFFFF 384 KB - Reserved

Extended Memory 0x00100000 - 0x7FFEFFFF ~2 GB - Usable
Kernel: 0x100000-0x200000 Frame Bitmap: ~32KB User Memory: Remainder
Memory-Mapped I/O 0x80000000 - 0xDFFFFFFF ~1.5 GB - Reserved PCI devices, APIC, Graphics memory
